<item>
            <title>[SPARK-6077] Multiple spark streaming tabs on UI when reuse the same sparkcontext</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6077</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we would create a new streaming tab for each streamingContext even if there&apos;s already one on the same sparkContext which would cause duplicate StreamingTab created and none of them is taking effect. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;snapshot: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dropbox.com/s/t4gd6hqyqo0nivz/bad%20multiple%20streamings.png?dl=0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.dropbox.com/s/t4gd6hqyqo0nivz/bad%20multiple%20streamings.png?dl=0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
1)&lt;br/&gt;
import org.apache.spark.SparkConf&lt;br/&gt;
import org.apache.spark.streaming.&lt;/p&gt;
{Seconds, StreamingContext}
&lt;p&gt;import org.apache.spark.storage.StorageLevel&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;val ssc = new StreamingContext(sc, Seconds(1))&lt;br/&gt;
val lines = ssc.socketTextStream(&quot;localhost&quot;, 9999, StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK_SER)&lt;br/&gt;
val words = lines.flatMap(_.split(&quot; &quot;))&lt;br/&gt;
val wordCounts = words.map(x =&amp;gt; (x, 1)).reduceByKey(_ + _)&lt;br/&gt;
wordCounts.print()&lt;br/&gt;
ssc.start()&lt;br/&gt;
.....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2)&lt;br/&gt;
ssc.stop(false)&lt;br/&gt;
val ssc = new StreamingContext(sc, Seconds(1))&lt;br/&gt;
val lines = ssc.socketTextStream(&quot;localhost&quot;, 9999, StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK_SER)&lt;br/&gt;
val words = lines.flatMap(_.split(&quot; &quot;))&lt;br/&gt;
val wordCounts = words.map(x =&amp;gt; (x, 1)).reduceByKey(_ + _)&lt;br/&gt;
wordCounts.print()&lt;br/&gt;
ssc.start()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
